<br>
With the new approach, that will no longer be true.  Your job will be to be handing a rod to each Cleric, every minute.  You are now going to be busy *during* the fight fucking around with rods.<br>
<br>
The rod change also kills Manaburn on raids.  A Wizard does more damage with regular nukes than with Manaburn.  Under the current approach, it is worth it to burn at the start of the fight (burn has very low aggro), and then use rods and other mana recovery methods to get mana back and nuke normally.  Without rods, the Wizard won't get enough mana back to nuke regularly after burning, and so the smart Wizard won't burn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unayanasoulspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nayana Soulspirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>~no rez for you~</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#333333>(10/10/02 4:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9516.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/kjdking/sigpic_12mini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rod Change and Manaburn</span><hr size=1> about the CH thing...   WTF are you people talking abotu  with focus items and AA we can make it heal for more... are you blind.  with the exception of extended range NO FOCUS ITEMS work on CH at all...    now unless they change that (which i doubt) there is no way to make CH heal for more than it allready does <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=160602 ><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/kjdking/sig9.JPG></a><br>
