Quote:<br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I wanna find out who claimed that monks, using no discipline, take LESS damage than a warrior using defensive. Then I would know who to aim my gales of laughter at, and who to hope never produces offspring, as I wouldn't want them contaminating the gene pool. If I am using stone stance, then yes, that is better than defensive. It also lasts, oh, what, 1/20 as long?<br>
<br>
I can assure you, and anyone else who doesn't know, that at least on Nameless, monks are *NOT* used to main tank any raid type mob whatsoever. None. Why? Cause warriors have up to &gt; 1k more HP than we do, making heals more efficient and giving a greater margin for error. Also, at least, if not more important, they have Defensive and Evasive, rendering them far far better tanks than us during the time of the disciplines, as if they weren't already. What we HAVE been used for is as a rampage tank, since we can use our EVADE to stay low on the main aggro list, yet stay at the top of the rampage list. This change will definitely screw that up, how much, we don't know yet.<br>
<br>
All I can say, ultimately, is that we'd better get SOMETHING as form of compensation. To just smack us with the nerf stick, and not give anything in return would really be screwing us over, hardcore. Really though, all this does iin the long run is to confirm my decision to hop over to WOW as soon as it actually gets to a playable stage.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Arlos the Disciple <br>
Legacy of Steel <br>
